Looking ahead from Week 47, several processes were already in motion. The Supreme Court was poised to rule on Trump\'92s tariff powers and on the scope of presidential control over independent agencies. Congress had passed a defense bill that both bolstered NATO and European security and demanded transparency on Caribbean strikes, setting up a test of whether the executive would comply. Illinois\'92s HB 1312 and similar state efforts would almost certainly face federal challenges, promising a constitutional fight over the limits of federal immigration enforcement. The AI preemption order created an AI Litigation Task Force whose work would soon begin to appear in court dockets. And the expiration of Affordable Care Act subsidies at the end of the month, after the Senate failed to extend them, threatened to double premiums for millions, with political and human consequences that would not be contained within a single week. The near future is already seeded.\
